				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Excellent comment Scarecrow.
<br />

<br />
To those who feel the same way, I would recommend putting aside any reservations you have about two boxing and give it a try if at all possible. For some, either via technical reasons or monetary reasons this might not be an option.
<br />

<br />
I did it in EQ-Live and now in EQ2. It has a MUCH greater effect in EQ2 as it opens up quite a bit of the grouping area access to me if I don't feel like playing with my friends for the evening. I combo a necromancer and an inquisitor (pure cleric).
<br />

<br />
Please note, I'm a grouper, not some solo only guy. But having the mini-group option gives me that freedom to explore and see just what I can do on my own.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: red"><span style="font-weight: bold">Heytred Incarnate of Blackburrow</span></span></span>
