				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In the short while ive played eq2 ive only found a few dissapointments (alot already said)
<br />

<br />
"Ninja" gathering. They should lock the thing your gathering from just like they do mobs you are fighting. (and if someone decides to walk away after 1 try, put some type of 10 second no activity timer on it or somethin)
<br />

<br />
Group EXP dept. There should be a better system with this. If some dumbass in my group wants to die, why should i suffer. This makes alot of people solo. I would be completly happy if there was no group dept. Some will say it makes the groups motavated to do better. I say, if a groups going to do good, they will, no matter what, and if theirs a dumbass there thats going to die, its going to happen, regardless of group exp dept or not. Ither take it away or make it better. Maybe a "group exp" dept bar. Seperate from your own exp bar. Something that only effects you while you group. Example. I join group 1. 2 people die, i get around 10% group exp debt. So i'm like fuck this, and disband. I go solo a bit, get regular exp, doesnt pay off the group debt. Then about a couple hours later i decide to group again. I get into group 2, start killing, and have my group exp dept slowly payed off before i gain any actual exp.
<br />

<br />
Spells + abilities. I dont know about yall but the 1 spell a lvl then having to upgrade up to 7 different times is just a pain in the ass. Instead of apprentice 2, 3, adept 1, 3, and master 1(will be to 4), they should just go apprentice, adept, and master. Apprentice, the pos you get when u first get the lvl, adept, something player made, and master, only found or quested for. Lots of problums ive seen with this actually. 
<br />

<br />
I also dont like the 1 per lvl thing and automatically getting them. I liked the fact that at certain lvl's i'd have to use the money ive saved to go out and buy a list of spells. Then i get to choose my stratagy baced on them.<br />_________________<br />Anyone want to start a Guild on the first eq2 pvp server that comes up?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
