				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As i said, time and money. If the apprentice 3 ect wernt their you could craft the adept spell, sell that, while going out to find master. Its like 6 versions of the exact same spell. If i was wanting an apprentice 3, why would i bother with 2. Its useless. If i was wanting an adept, why bother with any more apprentice? True they are cheaper, but the added costs of upgrading are much much more then if i was to skip a step. Ive gotten to where i only use mmy apprentice 1 spells when i get it (i still solo yellows, true its more casts = more mana used, but the downtime is still the same{maybe like 5 seconds more}) I'll save the money i get from selling vendor trash and upgrade from apprentice 1 to adept 1. I'll then wait for master to come along (maybe just MAYBE get adept 3, master is rare). 
<br />

